\par }\pard \s30\qj \li540\ri0\sa180\widctlpar\nooverflow\faroman\rin0\lin540\itap0\pararsid15402204 {\b\insrsid15402204 Auto Stop Timeout \endash }{\insrsid15402204  Some cameras only support a continuous mode of movem
ent. For instance you tell the camera to pan right and then when it is aligned correctly you tell it to stop. In some cases it is difficult to time this precisely over a web interface so this option allows you to specify an automatic timeout where the com
m
and will be automatically stopped. So a value of 0.25 here can tell the script to stop moving a quarter of a second after starting. This allows a more precise method of fine control. If this value is left blank or at zero it will be ignored, if set then i
t
